Financially caring for a baby is VERY hard, you need a good home, health insurance, a good job ext. By NO means am I assuming she will be a bad mother. I am just trying to convey worry for her and her partner, as I know people in my life who had gotten pregnant, kept the child, and lived a very very hard life afterwords. They do not regret having their child, but they regret not being prepared.
